---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="AudioSRT + Final Cut Pro — Free SRT Export" description="Generate frame-accurate SRT subtitle files for Final Cut Pro. Free, browser-based transcription with no upload required." canonical="https://audiosrt.com/integrations/final-cut-pro">
  <Header />
  <main class="lp-main">

    <section class="lp-hero">
      <span class="lp-badge">SRT · VTT — Final Cut Pro Compatible</span>
      <h1 class="lp-h1">AudioSRT for<br><span class="lp-accent">Final Cut Pro</span></h1>
      <p class="lp-intro">
        Final Cut Pro imports caption files through its Titles &amp; Generators workflow, and the timing has to be right — a caption file with loose or inaccurate timestamps will drift visibly against the picture. AudioSRT exports SRT files with millisecond-accurate timestamps derived from Whisper's word-level alignment, which means the file lands correctly on the FCP timeline without manual nudging.
      </p>
      <p class="lp-intro">
        The workflow is straightforward: transcribe in AudioSRT, export an SRT file, and import it into Final Cut Pro. Captions appear as a connected clip above your primary storyline, where you can adjust line breaks, timing, and individual cues directly in the timeline before sharing your final export.
      </p>
      <a href="/tool" class="lp-cta">Generate subtitles for Final Cut Pro →</a>
    </section>

    <section class="lp-steps-section" style="margin: 0 auto 48px;">
      <h2>How to use AudioSRT with Final Cut Pro</h2>
      <div class="lp-steps">
        <div class="lp-step">
          <div class="lp-step-num">01</div>
          <h3>Transcribe in AudioSRT</h3>
          <p>Upload your video or audio file. Whisper runs locally in your browser — client footage never leaves your machine. Edit the transcript for accuracy before exporting.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-step">
          <div class="lp-step-num">02</div>
          <h3>Export the SRT file</h3>
          <p>Download the SRT file with frame-accurate millisecond timestamps. The file is clean and validated — no formatting issues that would cause FCP's importer to reject it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-step">
          <div class="lp-step-num">03</div>
          <h3>Import into Final Cut Pro</h3>
          <p>Use File &gt; Import &gt; Captions in Final Cut Pro to bring in the SRT file. Captions appear as a connected clip above the primary storyline, ready to adjust and refine.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lp-detail">
      <h2>Final Cut Pro import — step by step</h2>
      <ol style="font-size: 14px; color: #3D3D3F; line-height: 2; padding-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 32px;">
        <li>In Final Cut Pro, open the project that contains your footage.</li>
        <li>Go to <strong>File &gt; Import &gt; Captions…</strong> from the menu bar.</li>
        <li>In the file picker, locate and select your exported <code>.srt</code> file.</li>
        <li>In the import dialog, choose the caption format: <strong>CEA-608</strong> for broadcast/delivery, or <strong>iTT (iTunes Timed Text)</strong> for Apple platforms.</li>
        <li>Click <strong>Import</strong>. The captions appear as a connected clip in a lane above the primary storyline.</li>
        <li>Click any caption cue to edit the text, adjust the timing, or reposition it on the timeline.</li>
        <li>When sharing, enable caption delivery in the Share dialog to embed or sidecar the captions in your export.</li>
      </ol>
      <p class="lp-body">
        If you receive an error on import, check that the SRT file uses UTF-8 encoding and that there are no overlapping timestamp ranges — AudioSRT exports clean files that pass this check by default.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="lp-features">
      <h2>Why editors use AudioSRT for FCP</h2>
      <div class="lp-feature-grid">
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">🎯</div>
          <h3>Frame-accurate timing</h3>
          <p>Millisecond-precise timestamps derived from Whisper's word-level alignment land correctly on the FCP timeline without manual offset correction.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">✏️</div>
          <h3>Edit before import</h3>
          <p>Review and correct the transcript in AudioSRT's editor before you export. The SRT you import into FCP is clean and intentional — not raw AI output.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">🔒</div>
          <h3>Client footage stays private</h3>
          <p>Everything runs in your browser. Client or unreleased footage is never sent to an external server — consistent with professional editorial confidentiality standards.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="lp-feature-card">
          <div class="lp-feature-icon">🆓</div>
          <h3>Free for audio</h3>
          <p>Audio-only transcription is free with no account required. Video transcription is available on the Starter plan with a 14-day free trial.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lp-cta-section">
      <h2>Generate subtitles for Final Cut Pro</h2>
      <p>Free for audio files.</p>
      <a href="/tool" class="lp-cta">Start for free →</a>
    </section>

  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.lp-main { font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; color: #1D1D1F; }
.lp-hero { text-align: center; padding: 80px 20px 60px; max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
.lp-badge { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; background: #EEEFFD; color: #6366F1; font-size: 12px; font-weight: 500; padding: 5px 14px; border-radius: 20px; border: 0.5px solid #C7C8F9; margin-bottom: 24px; }
.lp-h1 { font-size: clamp(28px, 4.5vw, 46px); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.15; letter-spacing: -0.8px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.lp-accent { color: #6366F1; }
.lp-intro { font-size: 15px; color: #6E6E73; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 32px; max-width: 560px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; }
.lp-cta { display: inline-block; background: #6366F1; color: #fff; padding: 13px 28px; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 500; text-decoration: none; transition: background 0.15s; }
.lp-cta:hover { background: #4F46E5; }
.lp-steps-section { padding: 64px 20px; max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; background: #F5F5F7; border-radius: 24px; text-align: center; }
.lp-steps-section h2 { font-size: 26px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 40px; letter-spacing: -0.5px; }
.lp-steps { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 32px; text-align: left; }
@media (max-width: 768px) { .lp-steps { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
.lp-step-num { font-size: 44px; font-weight: 800; color: #EEEFFD; letter-spacing: -2px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.lp-step h3 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.lp-step p { font-size: 13px; color: #6E6E73; line-height: 1.6; }
.lp-features { padding: 64px 20px; max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; }
.lp-features h2 { font-size: 26px; font-weight: 700; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 36px; letter-spacing: -0.5px; }
.lp-feature-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); gap: 20px; }
@media (max-width: 600px) { .lp-feature-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
.lp-feature-card { background: #fff; border: 0.5px solid #E5E5E7; border-radius: 14px; padding: 24px; }
.lp-feature-icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.lp-feature-card h3 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.lp-feature-card p { font-size: 13px; color: #6E6E73; line-height: 1.6; }
.lp-cta-section { text-align: center; padding: 64px 20px 80px; }
.lp-cta-section h2 { font-size: 24px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 8px; }
.lp-cta-section p { font-size: 14px; color: #6E6E73; margin-bottom: 24px; }
.lp-body { font-size: 14px; color: #3D3D3F; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 14px; }
.lp-detail { max-width: 680px; margin: 64px auto; padding: 0 20px; }
.lp-detail h2 { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.lp-inline-link { color: #6366F1; text-decoration: none; }
.lp-inline-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
</style>
